#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "Gametype:"
msgstr "Vrsta igre:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "Strategy, Dice"
msgstr "Strategija, kocke"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "Number of possible players:"
msgstr "Število možnih igralcev:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Two</para>"
msgstr "<para>Dva</para>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kjumpingcube; is a simple tactical game. You can play it against the "
"computer or a friend - or you can set up a game between two computer players "
"and just watch."
msgstr ""
"&kjumpingcube; je preprosta taktična igra. Lahko jo igrate proti računalniku "
"ali prijatelju - ali pa nastavite igro med dvema računalniškima igralcema in "
"samo gledate."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:79
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"That can be a good idea if you have not played &kjumpingcube; before. See "
"<link linkend=\"faq\">Frequently asked questions</link>, <quote>How do I get "
"started in this game?</quote>."
msgstr ""
"To je lahko dobra ideja, če še niste igrali &kjumpingcube; prej. Glejte "
"<link linkend=\"faq\">Pogosta vprašanja</link>, <quote>Kako začnem igrati to "
"igro?</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The playing area is a box of cubes containing points. When the game starts "
"each cube has one point, no owner and a neutral color. If you click on a "
"neutral cube it becomes yours, changes to your color and increases by one "
"point. Your objective is to capture all the cubes, but now it is your "
"opponent's turn."
msgstr ""
"Igralno območje je škatla s kockami, ki vsebujejo točke. Ko se igra začne, "
"ima vsaka kocka eno točko, brez lastnika in nevtralno barvo. Če kliknete na "
"nevtralno kocko, ta postane vaša, spremeni se v vašo barvo in se poveča za "
"eno točko. Vaš cilj je zajeti vse kocke, zdaj pa je na vrsti vaš nasprotnik."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:89
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Players move and add points by clicking on neutral cubes or their own cubes."
msgstr ""
"Igralci se premikajo in dodajajo točke s klikom na nevtralne kocke ali svoje "
"kocke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:92
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The only way to capture your opponent's cubes is to increase a cube's value "
"until it reaches a maximum and expands into neighboring cubes. Then those "
"cubes become yours, even if they belonged to your opponent before."
msgstr ""
"Edini način za zajemanje nasprotnikovih kock je povečanje vrednosti kocke, "
"dokler ne doseže največje vrednosti in se razširi na sosednje kocke. Potem "
"te kocke postanejo vaše, tudi če so prej pripadale vašemu nasprotniku."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:96
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sometimes a neighbor will also reach a maximum value and expand and a "
"cascade of moves will spread across the board. Large numbers of cubes can "
"suddenly change hands and this is where &kjumpingcube; becomes interesting "
"and challenging."
msgstr ""
"Včasih bo tudi sosed dosegel največjo vrednost in se razširil, po plošči pa "
"se bo razširila kaskada potez. Veliko število kock lahko nenadoma zamenja "
"lastnika in tukaj igra &kjumpingcube; postane zanimiva in zahtevna."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid "How to Play"
msgstr "Kako igrati"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:104
#, no-c-format
msgid "Objective:"
msgstr "Cilj:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:104
#, no-c-format
msgid "Take over all the cubes on the game board."
msgstr "Zavzemite vse kocke na igralni plošči."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kjumpingcube; loads directly into game mode, so you can start playing right "
"away. If Player 1 is a computer player, you must click to get started."
msgstr ""
"&kjumpingcube; naloži neposredno v igralni način, tako da lahko začnete "
"igrati takoj. Če je igralec 1 računalniški igralec, morate za začetek "
"klikniti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:109
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have not played &kjumpingcube; before, try watching a game or two "
"where the computer plays against itself. See <link linkend=\"faq"
"\">Frequently asked questions</link>, <quote>How do I get started in this "
"game?</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Če še niste igrali &kjumpingcube; prej si poskusite ogledati igro ali dve, "
"kjer računalnik igra sam proti sebi. Glejte <link linkend=\"faq\">Pogosta "
"vprašanja</link>, <quote>Kako začnem igrati to igro?</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You move by clicking on a neutral cube or one you already own. If you click "
"on a neutral cube, you gain ownership over it and the cube’s color changes "
"to your playing color. Each time you click on a cube, the value of the cube "
"increases by one. If the cube's value reaches a maximum, some of its points "
"move to the cube’s immediate neighbors (the points <quote>jump</quote> "
"around). If a neighboring cube happens to be owned by the other player, it "
"is captured, together with all of its points, and changes to your playing "
"color."
msgstr ""
"Premikate se s klikom na nevtralno kocko ali tisto, ki jo že imate. Če "
"kliknete nevtralno kocko, pridobite lastništvo nad njo in barva kocke se "
"spremeni v vašo igralno barvo. Vsakič, ko kliknete na kocko, se vrednost "
"kocke poveča za eno. Če vrednost kocke doseže največjo vrednost, se nekatere "
"njene točke premaknejo k neposrednim sosedom kocke (točke <quote>skačejo</"
"quote> naokoli). Če je sosednja kocka v lasti drugega igralca, je zajeta "
"skupaj z vsemi svojimi točkami in se spremeni v vašo igralno barvo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:115
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "Primer:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:115
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a cube in the centre reaches five points, four of its points go to its "
"four neighbors leaving the source cube with one point. It is possible to "
"start a cascade of automatic moves if any of the neighbors cubes also "
"reaches a maximum."
msgstr ""
"Če kocka v središču doseže pet točk, gredo štiri njene točke štirim sosedom, "
"izvorna kocka pa ostane z eno točko. Možno je sprožiti kaskado samodejnih "
"premikov, če tudi katera od sosednjih kock doseže maksimum."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid "Note:"
msgstr "Opomba:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Large parts of the playing area can change hands very rapidly. You can use "
"animation settings to help you follow what is happening then. See the <link "
"linkend=\"configuration\">Game Configuration</link> section for more details."
msgstr ""
"Veliki deli igrišča lahko zelo hitro zamenjajo lastnika. Z nastavitvami "
"animacije lahko spremljate dogajanje. Za več podrobnosti glejte razdelek "
"<link linkend=\"configuration\">Konfiguracija igre</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:119
#, no-c-format
msgid "The winner is the player who ends up owning all the cubes on the board."
msgstr "Zmagovalec je igralec, ki ima v lasti vse kocke na plošči."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:122
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game Rules, Strategies and Tips"
msgstr "Pravila igre, strategije in nasveti"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rules"
msgstr "Pravila"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A move consists of clicking on a cube that does not belong to your opponent."
msgstr ""
"Poteza je sestavljena iz klika na kocko, ki ne pripada vašemu nasprotniku."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "The move increases the points in the cube by one."
msgstr "Poteza poveča točke v kocki za eno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:128
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At the start of the game, each cube has one point, is painted in a neutral "
"color and has no owner."
msgstr ""
"Na začetku igre ima vsaka kocka eno točko, je pobarvana v nevtralno barvo in "
"nima lastnika."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "Each player has a color to mark the ownership of cubes."
msgstr "Vsak igralec ima barvo, s katero označi lastništvo kock."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By clicking a cube that has no owner, the player becomes the owner of that "
"cube and it changes its color to the player's color. Simultaneously the "
"cube’s value is increased by one."
msgstr ""
"S klikom na kocko, ki nima lastnika, postane igralec lastnik te kocke in ta "
"spremeni svojo barvo v barvo igralca. Hkrati se vrednost kocke poveča za eno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a cube has more points than it has neighbors, one point jumps to each of "
"the neighbors."
msgstr ""
"Če ima kocka več točk kot ima sosedov, ena točka skoči na vsakega od sosedov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"During such a move, all the neighboring cubes become owned by the player who "
"moved and so do all of their points, even if the neighbors were neutral or "
"owned by the other player."
msgstr ""
"Med takim premikom postanejo vse sosednje kocke v lasti igralca, ki se je "
"premaknil, in tudi vse njihove točke, tudi če so bile sosednje nevtralne ali "
"v lasti drugega igralca."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:133
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Neighbors are the cubes located above, below, at left or at right, but not "
"diagonally. Corner cubes have two neighbors, edge cubes have three and "
"center cubes have four."
msgstr ""
"Sosedje so kocke, ki se nahajajo zgoraj, spodaj, levo ali desno, vendar ne "
"diagonalno. Kotne kocke imajo dva soseda, robne kocke tri in sredinske štiri."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:134
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a move leaves a neighbor with a maximum number of points, the move "
"continues automatically to the neighbor's neighbors and so on, in a cascade. "
"A large number of cubes can change ownership during such a move."
msgstr ""
"Če premik zapusti soseda z največjim številom točk, se premik samodejno "
"nadaljuje do sosedovih sosedov in tako naprej, v kaskadi. Veliko število "
"kock lahko med takšno selitvijo zamenja lastništvo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:135
#, no-c-format
msgid "The winner is the player who ends up owning all the cubes."
msgstr "Zmagovalec je igralec, ki ima v lasti vse kocke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:136
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use settings to select board size, computer players, move animations "
"and players' colors. Each computer player can have its own style and skill "
"level. If not playing, it can provide hints to the corresponding human "
"player. You can also pit one computer player against another and watch the "
"outcome. See the <link linkend=\"configuration\">Game Configuration</link> "
"section for more details."
msgstr ""
"Z nastavitvami lahko izberete velikost plošče, računalniške igralce, "
"premikate animacije in barve igralcev. Vsak računalniški igralec ima lahko "
"svoj slog in raven spretnosti. Če ne igra, lahko daje namige ustreznemu "
"človeškemu igralcu. Lahko tudi pomerite enega računalniškega igralca z "
"drugim in opazujete izid. Za več podrobnosti glejte razdelek <link linkend="
"\"configuration\">Konfiguracija igre</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid "Strategies and Tips"
msgstr "Strategije in nasveti"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:142
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It may help to set up a computer v. computer game and select the check boxes "
"in the settings dialog that let you step through moves and animations at "
"your own pace. See <link linkend=\"faq\">Frequently asked questions</link>, "
"<quote>How do I get started in this game?</quote> and <quote>That was too "
"fast for me, how can I slow it down?</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Morda vam bo pomagalo, če nastavite računalniško proti računalniški igri in "
"izberete potrditvena polja v pogovornem oknu z nastavitvami, ki vam "
"omogočajo, da korakate skozi poteze in animacije v svojem tempu. Glejte "
"<link linkend=\"faq\">Pogosta vprašanja</link>, <quote>Kako naj začnem "
"igrati to igro?</quote> in <quote>To je bilo zame prehitro, kako naj ga "
"upočasnim ?</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:143
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have a cube which is right next to an opponent's cube, try to stay "
"ahead by increasing before your opponent does."
msgstr ""
"Če imate kocko, ki je tik ob nasprotnikovi kocki, poskušajte ostati v "
"prednosti tako, da povečate, preden to stori vaš nasprotnik."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If such a cube's points are less than or equal to the opponent's, try to "
"avoid increasing: you cannot win that arms race."
msgstr ""
"Če so točke takšne kocke manjše ali enake nasprotnikovim, se poskusite "
"izogniti povečanju: v tej oboroževalni tekmi ne morete zmagati."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Look for opportunities to increase and capture, but beware of your opponent "
"being able to reply by starting a cascade."
msgstr ""
"Iščite priložnosti za povečanje in zajemanje, vendar pazite, da bo vaš "
"nasprotnik lahko odgovoril z začetkom kaskade."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:146
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Try to get control of the corner cubes first, then the edge cubes. You need "
"fewer moves to make them reach a maximum and expand."
msgstr ""
"Poskusite najprej prevzeti nadzor nad kotnimi kockami, nato nad robnimi "
"kockami. Potrebujete manj potez, da dosežejo maksimum in se razširijo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:147
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Try not to play too close to your opponent, especially during the opening "
"moves. Drop back a cube or two or pick a cube on the diagonal from your "
"opponent."
msgstr ""
"Ne poskušajte igrati preblizu nasprotnika, še posebej med začetnimi "
"potezami. Spustite kocko ali dve nazaj ali izberite kocko na diagonali "
"nasprotnika."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:148
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Keep an eye out for long chains of cubes that are almost at their maximum. "
"If they are yours, you must guard them against cascading moves. If they are "
"your opponent's, they can become ripe for capture by a cascading move, just "
"as soon as they are close enough to your territory."
msgstr ""
"Bodite pozorni na dolge verige kock, ki so skoraj na svojem maksimumu. Če so "
"vaše, jih morate zaščititi pred kaskadnimi potezami. Če so nasprotnikove, "
"lahko postanejo zrele za ujetje s kaskadno potezo, takoj ko so dovolj blizu "
"vašemu ozemlju."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:153
#, no-c-format
msgid "Interface Overview"
msgstr "Pregled vmesnika"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:155
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Toolbar"
msgstr "Orodna vrstica"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:157
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Stop/Start Button"
msgstr "Gumb Stop/Start"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:159
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This large button appears at the top left of the toolbar and is used to "
"provide control over animations and computer moves, especially if the "
"computer has the first move, is playing against itself or is taking too long "
"to move. The button can also be used for stepping through a game or a move, "
"to let beginning players view each step at their own pace. Check boxes in "
"the settings dialog turn the step mode on or off (see the <link linkend="
"\"configuration\">Game Configuration</link> section for more details)."
msgstr ""
"Ta velik gumb se pojavi v zgornjem levem kotu orodne vrstice in se uporablja "
"za zagotavljanje nadzora nad animacijami in potezami računalnika, še "
"posebej, če ima računalnik prvi korak, igra sam s seboj ali če se premika "
"predolgo. Gumb lahko uporabite tudi za korakanje skozi igro ali potezo, tako "
"da lahko začetniki vidijo vsak korak v svojem tempu. Potrditvena polja v "
"pogovornem oknu z nastavitvami vklopijo ali izklopijo način korakov (za več "
"podrobnosti glejte razdelek <link linkend=\"configuration\">Konfiguracija "
"igre</link>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:168
#, no-c-format
msgid "The button has three states:"
msgstr "Gumb ima tri stanja:"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:171
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>Red</term>"
msgstr "<term>Rdeča</term>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to stop or interrupt a computer calculation, an animation or "
"a computer v. computer game."
msgstr ""
"Možno je ustaviti ali prekiniti računalniški izračun, animacijo ali "
"računalniško proti računalniški igrici."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:175
#, no-c-format
msgid "Green"
msgstr "Zelena"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:176
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to start or continue a computer move, an animation or a "
"computer v. computer game."
msgstr ""
"Možno je začeti ali nadaljevati računalniško potezo, animacijo ali "
"računalniško proti računalniški igrici."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:179
#, no-c-format
msgid "Blue"
msgstr "Modra"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:180
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The button is disabled and a human action is expected, such as making the "
"next move."
msgstr ""
"Gumb je onemogočen in pričakuje se človeško dejanje, na primer naslednji "
"korak."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:185
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In each case, the button contains some text to indicate what action can be "
"done or is expected, such as &nbsp;<guibutton>Stop animation</guibutton> or "
"<guibutton>Your turn</guibutton>."
msgstr ""
"V vsakem primeru gumb vsebuje nekaj besedila, ki nakazuje, katero dejanje je "
"mogoče izvesti ali se pričakuje, na primer &nbsp;<guibutton>Ustavi "
"animacijo</guibutton> ali <guibutton>Vi ste na vrsti</guibutton>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:189
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you stop the calculation of a computer move, the computer will pick the "
"best move it has so far. If you interrupt an animation (&eg; a cascade that "
"is taking too long), the move will proceed to its conclusion immediately."
msgstr ""
"Če ustavite izračun računalniške poteze, bo računalnik izbral najboljšo "
"potezo, ki jo ima do zdaj. Če prekinete animacijo (npr. kaskado, ki traja "
"predolgo), se bo poteza takoj zaključila."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:196
#, no-c-format
msgid "Standard Toolbar Buttons"
msgstr "Standardni gumbi orodne vrstice"

#. Tag: guiicon
#: index.docbook:198
#, no-c-format
msgid "Settings"
msgstr "Nastavitve"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:199
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A shortcut to enter the settings dialog and change playing conditions. See "
"the <link linkend=\"configuration\">Game Configuration</link> section for "
"more details."
msgstr ""
"Bližnjica za vstop v pogovorno okno z nastavitvami in spreminjanje pogojev "
"igranja. Za več podrobnosti glejte razdelek <link linkend=\"configuration"
"\">Konfiguracija igre</link>."

#. Tag: guiicon
#: index.docbook:201
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guiicon>New</guiicon>"
msgstr "<guiicon>Nova</guiicon>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:202 index.docbook:236
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start a new game."
msgstr "Začni novo igro."

#. Tag: guiicon
#: index.docbook:204
#, no-c-format
msgid "Load…"
msgstr "Naloži…"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:205 index.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid "Load a previously saved game."
msgstr "Naložite prej shranjeno igro."

#. Tag: guiicon
#: index.docbook:207
#, no-c-format
msgid "Save"
msgstr "Shrani"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:208 index.docbook:244
#, no-c-format
msgid "Save the current game."
msgstr "Shrani trenutno igro."

#. Tag: guiicon
#: index.docbook:210
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hint"
msgstr "Namig"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:211 index.docbook:278
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Get a hint as to the best move to make next. The hint is calculated by "
"computer player 1 or 2, depending on whether you are human player 1 or 2. "
"See the <link linkend=\"configuration\">Game Configuration</link> section "
"for more details."
msgstr ""
"Pridobite namig o najboljši naslednji potezi. Namig izračuna računalniški "
"igralec 1 ali 2, odvisno od tega, ali ste človeški igralec 1 ali 2. Za več "
"podrobnosti glejte razdelek <link linkend=\"configuration\">Konfiguracija "
"igre</link>."

#. Tag: guiicon
#: index.docbook:213
#, no-c-format
msgid "Undo"
msgstr "Razveljavi"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:214 index.docbook:263
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Undo a previous move, repeatedly if required. </action> Note: It is "
"possible to undo the closing moves of a completed game and investigate "
"alternative endings."
msgstr ""
"<action>Razveljavi prejšnjo potezo, po potrebi večkrat. </action> Opomba: "
"možno je razveljaviti zaključne poteze končane igre in raziskati druge konce."

#. Tag: guiicon
#: index.docbook:218
#, no-c-format
msgid "Redo"
msgstr "Ponovi"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:219 index.docbook:271
#, no-c-format
msgid "Redo a move that was undone, repeatedly if required."
msgstr "Ponovite potezo, ki je bila razveljavljena, po potrebi večkrat."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid "Menu Items"
msgstr "Elementi menija"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:231
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Game Menu"
msgstr "Meni igre"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:233
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\"> &Ctrl;<keycap>N</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Game</guimenu><guimenuitem>New</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\"> &Ctrl;<keycap>N</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Igra</guimenu><guimenuitem>Nova</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:238
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>O</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Game</guimenu><guimenuitem>Load…</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>O</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Igra</guimenu><guimenuitem>Naloži…</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:242
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>S</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Game</guimenu><guimenuitem>Save</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>S</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Igra</guimenu><guimenuitem>Shrani</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:246
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Game</guimenu><guimenuitem>Save As…</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Igra</guimenu><guimenuitem>Shrani kot…</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:248
#, no-c-format
msgid "Save the current game with a different name."
msgstr "Shranite trenutno igro z drugim imenom."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:250
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>Q</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Game</guimenu><guimenuitem>Quit</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>Q</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Igra</guimenu><guimenuitem>Zapusti</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:252
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Quit</action> &kjumpingcube;."
msgstr "<action>Zapusti</action> &kjumpingcube;."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:258
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Move Menu"
msgstr "Meni Premakni"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut> <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>Z</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Move</guimenu><guimenuitem>Undo</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut> <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>Z</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Premakni</guimenu><guimenuitem>Razveljavi</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:268
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Shift;<keycap>Z</keycap></"
"keycombo></shortcut> <guimenu>Move</guimenu><guimenuitem>Redo</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Shift;<keycap>Z</keycap></"
"keycombo></shortcut> <guimenu>Premakni</guimenu><guimenuitem>Ponovi</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:275
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycap>H</keycap></shortcut> <guimenu>Move</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Hint</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycap>H</keycap></shortcut> <guimenu>Premakni</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Namig</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:287
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other Menus"
msgstr "Drugi meniji"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:288
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Additionally &kjumpingcube; has the common &kde; <guimenu>Settings</guimenu> "
"and <guimenu>Help</guimenu> menu items, for more information read the "
"sections about the <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus.html#menus-settings"
"\">Settings Menu</ulink> and <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus."
"html#menus-help\">Help Menu</ulink> of the &kde; Fundamentals."
msgstr ""
"Poleg tega &kjumpingcube; ima skupno &kde; Elemente menija "
"<guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu> in <guimenu>Pomoč</guimenu>, za več informacij "
"preberite razdelke o <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus.html#menus-"
"settings\">meniju z nastavitvami</ulink> in <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/"
"menus.html#menus-help\">meni Pomoč</ulink> v &kde; Osnove."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:301
#, no-c-format
msgid "Frequently asked questions"
msgstr "Pogosto zastavljena vprašanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:306
#, no-c-format
msgid "I want to change the way this game looks. Can I?"
msgstr "Želim spremeniti videz te igre. Ali lahko?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:307
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Currently you can only change the player's colors, but not the game theme. "
"To change the player's colors use the <link linkend=\"configuration\">Game "
"Configuration</link> dialog."
msgstr ""
"Trenutno lahko spremenite samo barve igralca, ne pa tudi teme igre. Če "
"želite spremeniti barve igralca, uporabite pogovorno okno <link linkend="
"\"configuration\">Konfiguracija igre</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:310
#, no-c-format
msgid "How do I get started in this game?"
msgstr "Kako naj začnem igrati to igro?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:311
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The moves of &kjumpingcube; can be hard to follow at first. One way to learn "
"is to watch games where the computer plays against itself. Use the <link "
"linkend=\"configuration\">Game Configuration</link> dialog to set it up. "
"Check both <guilabel>Playing now</guilabel> boxes, choose a board size in "
"the range 3x3 to 5x5, set the animation to <guilabel>Scatter dots</guilabel> "
"and the move-time to <guilabel>Long</guilabel>, then click <guibutton>OK</"
"guibutton>. Now click the big green button in the toolbar to start the game."
msgstr ""
"Poteze &kjumpingcube; na začetku je težko slediti. Eden od načinov učenja je "
"gledanje iger, v katerih igra računalnik sam proti sebi. Za nastavitev "
"uporabite pogovorno okno <link linkend=\"configuration\">Konfiguracija igre</"
"link>. Označite obe polji <guilabel>Igranje zdaj</guilabel>, izberite "
"velikost plošče v razponu od 3x3 do 5x5, nastavite animacijo na "
"<guilabel>Razpršene pike</guilabel> in čas premikanja na <guilabel>Dolgo</"
"guilabel >, nato kliknite <guibutton>V redu</guibutton>. Zdaj kliknite velik "
"zeleni gumb v orodni vrstici, da začnete igro."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:320
#, no-c-format
msgid "That was too fast for me, how can I slow it down?"
msgstr "To je bilo zame prehitro, kako naj to upočasnim?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:321
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the <link linkend=\"configuration\">Game Configuration</link> dialog "
"again. Down at the bottom are two check boxes. Check one to pause the game "
"between moves. Check the other to pause between steps of cascade moves that "
"spread out over the board, especially near the end of the game. Back in the "
"game, you can now use the big toolbar button (whenever it goes green), to "
"trigger off each move or proceed step by step within a move, at whatever "
"pace you choose."
msgstr ""
"Ponovno uporabite pogovorno okno <link linkend=\"configuration"
"\">Konfiguracija igre</link>. Na dnu sta dve potrditveni polji. Označite "
"enega, da igro prekinete med potezami. Označite drugo, da se ustavite med "
"koraki kaskadnih potez, ki se razprostirajo po plošči, zlasti proti koncu "
"igre. V igri lahko zdaj uporabite velik gumb v orodni vrstici (kadar koli "
"postane zelen), da sprožite vsako potezo ali nadaljujete korak za korakom "
"znotraj poteze, ne glede na hitrost, ki jo izberete."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:330
#, no-c-format
msgid "What does the big button in the toolbar do?"
msgstr "Kaj počne velik gumb v orodni vrstici?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:331
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This button is used to stop something the computer is doing (red color), "
"start or continue a computer action when you are ready (green color) or "
"prompt you to do something, such as make a move (blue color, button "
"disabled). For a full description see <link linkend=\"stop_start_button"
"\">The Stop/Start Button</link>."
msgstr ""
"Ta gumb se uporablja za ustavitev nečesa, kar računalnik počne (rdeča "
"barva), za začetek ali nadaljevanje dejanja računalnika, ko ste pripravljeni "
"(zelena barva) ali za poziv, da nekaj storite, na primer naredite potezo "
"(modra barva, gumb onemogočen). Za celoten opis glejte <link linkend="
"\"stop_start_button\">Gumb Stop/Start</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:339
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can I use the keyboard to play the game?"
msgstr "Ali lahko uporabljam tipkovnico za igranje igre?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:340
#, no-c-format
msgid "No. &kjumpingcube; cannot be played using the keyboard."
msgstr "Ne. &kjumpingcube; ni mogoče predvajati s tipkovnico."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid "Where are the high scores?"
msgstr "Kje so visoki rezultati?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:345
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kjumpingcube; does not have such a feature."
msgstr "&kjumpingcube; nima take funkcije."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:352
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game Configuration"
msgstr "Konfiguracija igre"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:355
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To open the configuration dialog use the <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Configure &kjumpingcube;…</guimenuitem></menuchoice> "
"menu item, on Apple Mac OS X use the <menuchoice><guimenu>&kjumpingcube;</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Preferences</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item, or "
"you can use the <guibutton>Settings</guibutton> button in the toolbar."
msgstr ""
"Če želite odpreti konfiguracijsko pogovorno okno, uporabite menijski element "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj "
"&kjumpingcube;…</guimenuitem></menuchoice>, v sistemu Apple Mac OS X "
"uporabite <menuchoice><guimenu >&kjumpingcube;</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Nastavitve</guimenuitem></menuchoice>, lahko pa uporabite gumb "
"<guibutton>Nastavitve</guibutton> v orodni vrstici."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:358
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>&kjumpingcube; Settings</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>&kjumpingcube; Nastavitve</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:361
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>&kjumpingcube; Settings</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&kjumpingcube; Nastavitve</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:365
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Cascade Move Display and Cascade Move Time panels control the optional "
"animation display when a cube reaches its maximum and spills over into "
"neighboring cubes, possibly starting an extended cascade of moves. It is "
"easiest at first to use the <quote>Scatter dots</quote> animation and a long "
"move time. That is the best way to follow the progress of cascade moves. The "
"two Pause check boxes let you step through animations and computer moves at "
"your own pace."
msgstr ""
"Plošči Prikaz kaskadnih premikov in Čas kaskadnih premikov nadzorujeta "
"izbirni prikaz animacije, ko kocka doseže svoj maksimum in se prelije na "
"sosednje kocke, kar lahko sproži razširjeno kaskado premikov. Na začetku je "
"najlažje uporabiti animacijo <quote>Razpršene pike</quote> in dolg čas "
"premikanja. To je najboljši način za spremljanje napredka kaskadnih potez. "
"Dve potrditveni polji Premor vam omogočata, da se premikate skozi animacije "
"in premikanje računalnika v svojem tempu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:367
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Computer Player 1 and 2 panels control the style and level of each "
"computer player's play and whether that player should actually play or just "
"provide hints to human player 1 or 2."
msgstr ""
"Plošči Računalniški igralec 1 in 2 nadzorujeta slog in raven igranja vsakega "
"računalniškega igralca ter ali naj ta igralec dejansko igra ali samo daje "
"namige človeškemu igralcu 1 ali 2."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:370
#, no-c-format
msgid "Details of Settings"
msgstr "Podrobnosti o nastavitvah"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:372
#, no-c-format
msgid "Playing now"
msgstr "Igranje zdaj"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:373
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sets Computer Player 1 or 2 to be actively playing or just assisting a human "
"player with hints. Normally you would set the computer to play one player "
"and you would play the other, but you can have two human players or two "
"computer players and just watch. Player 1 always starts first."
msgstr ""
"Računalniškega igralca 1 ali 2 nastavi tako, da aktivno igra ali samo pomaga "
"človeškemu igralcu z namigi. Običajno bi računalnik nastavili tako, da igra "
"enega igralca, vi pa drugega, lahko pa imate dva človeška igralca ali dva "
"računalniška igralca in samo gledate. Igralec 1 vedno začne prvi."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:375
#, no-c-format
msgid "Style of Play"
msgstr "Slog igre"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:376
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sets Computer Player 1 or 2 to play as Kepler or Newton. Kepler chooses "
"moves by the same method as earlier versions of &kjumpingcube;. Newton uses "
"a different method."
msgstr ""
"Nastavi računalniškega igralca 1 ali 2, da igra kot Kepler ali Newton. "
"Kepler izbira poteze po enaki metodi kot prejšnje različice &kjumpingcube;. "
"Newton uporablja drugačno metodo."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:378
#, no-c-format
msgid "Computer Skill"
msgstr "Računalniška spretnost"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:379
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Lets you choose a computer player's playing skill from a slider.</"
"action> This decides how clever the computer opponent will be."
msgstr ""
"<action>Omogoča vam, da iz drsnika izberete igralne sposobnosti "
"računalniškega igralca.</action> Ta določa, kako spreten bo računalniški "
"nasprotnik."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:380
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can choose any of five levels, ranging from <guilabel>Beginner</"
"guilabel>, through <guilabel>Average</guilabel> to <guilabel>Expert</"
"guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Izberete lahko katero koli od petih stopenj, od <guilabel>Začetnika</"
"guilabel>, preko <guilabel>Povprečja</guilabel> do <guilabel>Eksperta</"
"guilabel>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:382
#, no-c-format
msgid "Board Size"
msgstr "Velikost plošče"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:383
#, no-c-format
msgid "Lets you choose the size of the play area."
msgstr "Omogoča izbiro velikosti igrišča."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:384
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the slider to select a value between <guilabel>3x3</guilabel> cubes and "
"<guilabel>15x15</guilabel> cubes. The range 5x5 to 9x9 is the most "
"convenient. Below 5x5 it is very hard to beat the computer. Above 9x9 games "
"can become rather long."
msgstr ""
"Z drsnikom izberite vrednost med kockami <guilabel>3x3</guilabel> in kockami "
"<guilabel>15x15</guilabel>. Razpon od 5x5 do 9x9 je najprimernejši. Pod 5x5 "
"je zelo težko premagati računalnik. Igre nad 9x9 lahko postanejo precej "
"dolge."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:386
#, no-c-format
msgid "Players' Colors"
msgstr "Barve igralcev"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:387
#, no-c-format
msgid "Choose a color for each player and for the neutral cubes."
msgstr "Izberite barvo za vsakega igralca in za nevtralne kocke."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:389
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cascade Move Display"
msgstr "Prikaz kaskadnih premikov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:390
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choose an animation style for when a cube reaches its maximum and expands "
"into neighboring cubes, possibly starting a cascade of such moves and "
"covering a large area of the board."
msgstr ""
"Izberite slog animacije, ko kocka doseže svoj maksimum in se razširi na "
"sosednje kocke, po možnosti sproži kaskado takih potez in pokrije veliko "
"površino plošče."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:391
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the radio buttons to select from <guilabel>None (no pauses)</guilabel>, "
"where the whole move is displayed instantaneously; <guilabel>Darken and "
"pause</guilabel>, where each overloaded cube darkens until it is time for it "
"to expand; <guilabel>Blink rapidly</guilabel>, where each overloaded cube "
"darkens at first and then blinks rapidly when it is time for it to expand "
"and <guilabel>Scatter dots</guilabel>, where each overloaded cube darkens at "
"first and then fires dots into neighboring cubes when it is time for it to "
"expand."
msgstr ""
"Z izbirnimi gumbi izberite <guilabel>Brez (brez premorov)</guilabel>, kjer "
"je celoten premik prikazan v trenutku; <guilabel>Zatemni in ustavi</"
"guilabel>, kjer vsaka preobremenjena kocka potemni, dokler ni čas, da se "
"razširi; <guilabel>Hitro utripanje</guilabel>, kjer vsaka preobremenjena "
"kocka najprej potemni in nato hitro utripa, ko je čas, da se razširi, in "
"<guilabel>Razpršene pike</guilabel>, kjer vsaka preobremenjena kocka najprej "
"potemni in se nato sproži pike v sosednje kocke, ko je čas, da se razširi."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:393
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cascade Move Time"
msgstr "Čas kaskadnih premikov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:394
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the slider to select from a range of times (<guilabel>Short</guilabel> "
"to <guilabel>Long</guilabel>) to be spent on animations. The times depend a "
"little on the type of animation, but can range from 0.15 seconds to 1.5 "
"seconds for each stage of a cascade move."
msgstr ""
"Z drsnikom izberite čas (<guilabel>Kratek</guilabel> do <guilabel>Dolg</"
"guilabel>), ki bo porabljen za animacije. Časi so nekoliko odvisni od vrste "
"animacije, vendar se lahko gibljejo od 0,15 sekunde do 1,5 sekunde za vsako "
"stopnjo kaskadnega premika."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:396
#, no-c-format
msgid "Pause before each computer move"
msgstr "Premor pred vsakim premikanjem računalnika"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:397
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this check box is selected, computer players will pause before they start "
"a move, until you click to resume. This is to help you follow the action, "
"especially if you are a new player or studying a computer versus computer "
"game."
msgstr ""
"Če je to potrditveno polje izbrano, se bodo računalniški igralci začasno "
"ustavili, preden začnejo potezo, dokler ne kliknete za nadaljevanje. To vam "
"pomaga slediti dogajanju, še posebej, če ste nov igralec ali preučujete igro "
"računalnik proti računalniku."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:399
#, no-c-format
msgid "Pause before each cascade step"
msgstr "Premor pred vsakim kaskadnim korakom"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:400
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this check box is selected, the animation of cascade moves will pause "
"between steps, until you click to resume. This is to help you observe such a "
"move as it spreads out over the board."
msgstr ""
"Če je to potrditveno polje izbrano, se bo animacija kaskadnih premikov "
"ustavila med koraki, dokler ne kliknete za nadaljevanje. To vam bo pomagalo "
"opazovati takšno potezo, ko se razprostira po plošči."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:407
#, no-c-format
msgid "Credits and License"
msgstr "Zasluge in licenca"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:410
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kjumpingcube; is Copyright 2012, 2013 Ian Wadham and Copyright 1998, 1999 "
"&Matthias.Kiefer; &Matthias.Kiefer.mail;"
msgstr ""
"&kjumpingcube; je Copyright 2012, 2013 Ian Wadham in Copyright 1998, 1999 "
"&Matthias.Kiefer; &Matthias.Kiefer.mail;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:413
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kjumpingcube; was inspired by a game that came out for the Commodore 64 and "
"other early home computers. Unfortunately the original author's name is "
"unknown."
msgstr ""
"&kjumpingcube; je navdihnila igra, ki je izšla za Commodore 64 in druge "
"zgodnje domače računalnike. Na žalost izvirno ime avtorja ni znano."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:417
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In 2007, Ian Wadham took over maintenance of &kjumpingcube; for &kde; 4 and "
"Eugene Trounev painted the first &SVG; theme."
msgstr ""
"Leta 2007 je Ian Wadham prevzel vzdrževanje &kjumpingcube; za &kde; 4 in "
"Eugene Trounev sta naslikala prvi &SVG; tema."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:420
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In 2012 and 2013, Ian developed versions 2.0 and 2.1 of &kjumpingcube;, "
"adding the animation styles, allowing board sizes down to 3x3 or up to 15x15 "
"and writing completely new artificial intelligence modules that offer more "
"of a challenge to a human player. These versions calculate moves faster, add "
"multi-level undo/redo (previously only one move), add a choice of two AI "
"opponents and provide options for beginning players to step through "
"animations and computer moves."
msgstr ""
"V letih 2012 in 2013 je Ian razvil različici 2.0 in 2.1 &kjumpingcube;, "
"dodal sloge animacije, dovolil velikosti plošč do 3x3 ali do 15x15 in "
"napisal popolnoma nove module umetne inteligence, ki človeškemu igralcu "
"ponujajo večji izziv. Te različice hitreje izračunajo poteze, dodajo "
"razveljavitev/ponovitev na več ravneh (prej le eno potezo), dodajo možnost "
"izbire dveh nasprotnikov z umetno inteligenco in ponujajo možnosti za "
"igralce začetnike, da stopijo skozi animacije in računalniške poteze."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:422
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Documentation Copyright 2012, 2013 Ian Wadham and Copyright 1999 &Matthias."
"Kiefer; &Matthias.Kiefer.mail;"
msgstr ""
